.TH "of_modalias_node" 9 "of_modalias_node" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_modalias_node \- Lookup appropriate modalias for a device node
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_modalias_node
.BI "(struct device_node *node "  ","
.BI "char *modalias "  ","
.BI "int len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "node" 12
pointer to a device tree node
.IP "modalias" 12
Pointer to buffer that modalias value will be copied into
.IP "len" 12
Length of modalias value
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Based on the value of the compatible property, this routine will attempt
to choose an appropriate modalias value for a particular device tree node.
It does this by stripping the manufacturer prefix (as delimited by a ',')
from the first entry in the compatible list property.

This routine returns 0 on success, <0 on failure.
